        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 5:48PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cushman, or 11 miles northwest of Batesville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aetna...                          Maxville...
Charlotte...                      Smithville...
Calamine...                       Mount Pleasant...
Gainesboro...                     Batesville...
Cave City...                      Pfeiffer...
Moorefield...                     Dowdy...
Strawberry...                     Lafferty...
Sulphur Rock...                   Elgin...
Bethesda...                       Sandtown...
Cord...                           Cushman...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
